  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-02 test)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This package references an external hemolysis correlation study (Giersiepen et al., re-examined by Fraser et al.) as a normative anchor for the power-law damage model; the reference is recorded via referencesIdentifier but the corresponding bibliographic node is not inlined in this package graph.",
